  "prompt": "Is there a great Android app that let's you write concert music easily?",
  "response": "There are several music composition apps available for Android that can help you write concert music. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. MuseScore (Free)\n- Professional notation software\n- Create, edit, and play sheet music\n- Available on desktop and mobile\n\n2. Notion (Paid)\n- High-quality music notation app\n- Advanced composition features\n- Good for professional composers\n\n3. Flat.io (Free/Paid)\n- Web and mobile music notation\n- Collaboration features\n- Easy to use interface\n\n4. Symphony Pro (Paid)\n- Professional music composition\n- MIDI input support\n- Comprehensive notation tools\n\n5. Perfect Piano (Free)\n- Virtual piano for composition\n- Recording capabilities\n- MIDI export\n\n6. GarageBand (Free, iOS only)\n- While primarily for iOS, it offers great music creation tools\n- Android alternatives like Caustic 3 provide similar functionality\n\nEach app has different strengths, so I recommend trying a few to see which best suits your specific composition needs and workflow.",
